I may be missing something, but was thinking this:

```dart
// The callback passed to `new Future` is passed to Timer.run.
final String rawLicenses = await new Future<String>(
  () => rootBundle.loadString('LICENSE', cache: false),
);
final List<LicenseEntry> parsedLicenses = await new Future<List<LicenseEntry>>(
  () => compute(_parseLicenses, rawLicenses, debugLabel: 'parseLicenses'),
);
```

Or to put it another way, there's no difference between your code and:
```dart
final String rawLicenses = await rootBundle.loadString('LICENSE', cache: false);
final List<LicenseEntry> parsedLicenses = await compute(_parseLicenses, rawLicenses, debugLabel: 'parseLicenses');
```
...which is what it was before. :-)

